### Heading hierarchy

- **Level 1 (`#`)**: Only for the README title (e.g., project or script name).
- **Level 2 (`##`)**: Required sections (Overview, Prerequisites, Usage, API, etc.).
- **Level 3 (`###`)**: Subsections within a section (e.g., â€œQuery parametersâ€, â€œResponse fieldsâ€).

